{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55356 ?\u57272 ? Import MusicXML\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script imports an uncompressed MusicXML file (e.g., from Guitar Pro) into REAPER, preserving string/fret positions via MIDI channels and text events. It's designed to work seamlessly with {\b ReaTab Hero}, eliminating the need to manually reassign strings and frets after exporting MIDI.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Parses {\f1 <string>} and {\f1 <fret>} elements and maps string numbers to MIDI channels (string 1 \u8594 ? channel 7, etc.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Converts fret numbers and articulations (slides, hammer-ons, harmonics, mutes, etc.) into text or marker events\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Handles drum parts with configurable per\u8209 ?family channel mapping\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Expands repeats (forward/backward) and respects chord offsets\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optionally imports tempo and time signature markers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Creates separate MIDI tracks for each staff\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Three insertion modes}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Create new tracks}: original behavior \u8211- creates a new track for each staff.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Insert on existing tracks}: places MIDI items on currently selected tracks (one staff per selected track, in order).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Match tracks by name}: automatically maps staves to existing tracks based on track names (e.g., "Guitar", "Bass", etc.).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Stores string tuning as track ExtState for compatibility with ReaTab Hero (ensures correct display of tablature).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Via ReaPack (recommended)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab In REAPER, open {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Import Repositories}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Paste this link - https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kkonstantin2000/konst_reascripts/master/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Click {\b OK}, then {\b Synchronize}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Find the script in the Action List: {\f1 Script: konst_Import MusicXML.lua}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Manual\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Download {\f1 konst_Import MusicXML.lua} from the {\f1 ImportMusicXML} folder and place it in your REAPER Scripts directory.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Run the script from the Action List.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Press button "Select File" and select uncompressed {\f1 .xml} file (MusicXML) in File Explorer.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Choose whether to import tempo/time signature markers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab New tracks will be created with MIDI items containing notes and text events.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For best results with ReaTab Hero, make sure the target track has the proper string tuning set (the script can now store tuning as track ExtState \u8211- see below).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Feedback & Contributions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Found a bug? Have a feature request? Please open an issue on GitHub or post in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=307042"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
REAPER forum thread
}}}
.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Credits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Thanks to {\b ExtremRaym} for ReaTab Hero and for encouraging this project.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Inspired by the REAPER scripting community.\sa180\par}
}
